Github Commands



Git init

Git add .

git commit -m “ message “

Git push origin master

Git branch 

Git checkout <branch>

Git stash

Git branch -f master HEAD~3

Git cherry-pick <commit1> <commit2>

git config --global user.name <username>

git config --global user.email <email>

git push origin HEAD:refs/for/master     # for pushing in vista Gerrit repo

Git checkout -b <branchname>.  # to create a new branch as well as checking it out

git checkout -b <new-branch> <existing-branch> # creates a new branch from the existing-branch









